      <!-- ===== Scenario Reference ===== -->
      <details class="scenario-box" open>
        <summary class="cursor-pointer font-semibold text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200 select-none">Scenario (click to collapse)</summary>
        <div class="mt-3 text-sm leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 space-y-3">
          <p>A family-run screw manufacturer (a medium enterprise) that is a world market leader in a specialized type of wood screws has come up with a new idea to incorporate sensors into their screws. The sensors will be able to detect when a screw is being over-stressed, losing pressure, or experiencing any other issues, and will send out an alert to the relevant parties.</p>
          <p>The company has built a reputation for producing high-quality and reliable screws used in construction, manufacturing, aerospace, and defense. As demand has grown, the company has become concerned about screws failing in the field, leading to costly downtime and repairs. When asking companies which suffered from costly downtime and repairs, 90% of those customers reported they would pay up to 100x the price for an improved screw.</p>
          <p>An American researcher published a paper on a novel micro-sensor technology (MiSe), which received very little attention yet. The company's management decided to invest in MiSe development to integrate it into screws. The sensors detect when a screw approaches maximum load capacity and alert maintenance crews or engineers.</p>
          <p>The sensors will be small, low-power, and highly reliable, communicating via Bluetooth or wireless technologies for real-time data analysis. The system can be configured depending on risk tolerance.</p>
          <p>The company sees this as product differentiation and aims to increase customer satisfaction and safety. They also want to include a <strong>hidden feature to track customer usage data</strong>. They plan to offer the sensor-enabled screw as an upgrade and new product, and to <strong>patent the technology</strong>.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

